b'' b'musselman) wrote:' b'' b' i need to find a uart that will interface to an and do the following:' b' \t-250k baud, data bits, stop bits, no parity' b' \t-ability to do break detect (irq or output pin)' b' \t-irq on character received' b'' b" i'm using a dallas ds2250 at mhz clone), but it won't do" b" break detect. i've looked at the etc..." b'' b' \tany help would be appriciated!!!' b'' b'actually detecting a break is done by watching for a "character" containing' b'all zero bits with the framing error resulting from its receipt. this' b'means that the line stayed in the zero bit state even past the stop bit' b'time slot, which basically indicates a break. there is no special way to' b"detect break that i have found other than this there's no magic signal" b'generated by uarts, etc.' b'' b'portable macintosh software group pretty worthless, but' b'apple computer they *are* my own...' b'art without engineering is dreaming. engineering without art is' b'calculating.' b'-- steven k. roberts in "computing across america"' 